{
 "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
 "$id": "schema:event",
 "$comment": "An authored event record (ADR-019, gh #39/#40): a declarative trigger + a nested-block command list. The trigger-kind and command enums are extended wave by wave — each kind/command lands with the Kanto beat that demands it (ADR-019 §6), and the runtime VM refuses at boot any kind, command, or condition it cannot execute, so this schema and the interpreter move together. `visible` triggers are load-time QUERIES (visible_when decides a map object's visibility), never command runs; `step` dispatch is (map, cell)-indexed at load. Conditions (`visible_when`, `when`, `if.cond`) are FormulaExpr strings whose bare identifiers read story flags (1/0) and event vars, plus the engine-state vocabulary `item_<id>` (bag count), `badge_<name>`, `badge_count`, `force_bike`, `surfing`, `player_x`/`player_y` (the player's cell), `dex_owned`, and `defeated_<x>_<y>` (the trainer at home cell (x, y) on the RECORD'S map). Beat args also accept `@object:<key>` for a named map object. A `battle_end` trigger with `rerun_enter: true` re-runs the map's enter records first — pokered's EndTrainerBattle re-running the load callback, so a door opens the moment its last guard falls. `say` is a blocking dialogue page; `notice` is the one-shot non-blocking textbox (a guard's line after a push-back — the event ends without waiting for the dismissal). Text may hold {player}/{rival} placeholders; \\n is a line break, \\f a page break, as v1's text engine reads them. `beat` invokes a native Cutscene beat by name (the strangler-fig seam while wave C dissolves story beats; ceremonies stay native forever); the arg \"@npc\" resolves to the triggering NPC.",
 "type": "object",
 "required": [
  "id",
  "trigger"
 ],
 "properties": {
  "$comment": {
   "type": "string"
  },
  "id": {
   "type": "string",
   "pattern": "^event:[a-z0-9_]+$"
  },
  "trigger": {
   "type": "object",
   "required": [
    "kind",
    "map"
   ],
   "properties": {
    "kind": {
     "enum": [
      "interact",
      "visible",
      "enter",
      "step",
      "battle_end",
      "boulder_hole",
      "boulder",
      "warp"
     ]
    },
    "dest": {
     "type": "string",
     "x-ref": "map"
    },
    "at": {
     "type": "array",
     "items": {
      "$ref": "#/$defs/cell"
     }
    },
    "map": {
     "type": "string",
     "x-ref": "map"
    },
    "object": {
     "type": "string"
    },
    "visible_when": {
     "type": "string"
    },
    "when": {
     "type": "string"
    },
    "front": {
     "type": "array",
     "items": {
      "$ref": "#/$defs/cell"
     }
    },
    "cells": {
     "type": "array",
     "items": {
      "$ref": "#/$defs/cell"
     }
    },
    "region": {
     "type": "array",
     "items": {
      "type": "integer"
     },
     "minItems": 4,
     "maxItems": 4
    },
    "facing": {
     "enum": [
      "down",
      "up",
      "left",
      "right"
     ]
    },
    "consume": {
     "type": "boolean"
    },
    "rerun_enter": {
     "type": "boolean"
    }
   },
   "additionalProperties": false
  },
  "commands": {
   "$ref": "#/$defs/block"
  },
  "custom": {
   "type": "object"
  }
 },
 "additionalProperties": false,
